{"_id":"hAXKBzA7qabr3pvE","name":"INFLUENCE Over ?","permission":{"default":0,"PIYJckcNzA7ukurN":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Take +1 to all moves targeting the character who gave you this card.</p>\n<p><strong>When you take advantage of this Influence, return this card to the character who gave it to you and choose one:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Inflict a condition on them, your choice.</li>\n<li>They take -2 on a move they just made (after their roll).</li>\n<li>Take an additional +1 on a move targeting them (after your roll).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you would get another Influence card from the same character, instead immediately shift 1 of their Labels up and 1 of their Labels down, your choice.</p>","requiresMove":"","moveType":"","moveGroup":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"key":"data.moveResults.failure.value","label":"Complications...","value":""},"partial":{"key":"data.moveResults.partial.value","label":"Partial success","value":""},"success":{"key":"data.moveResults.success.value","label":"Success!","value":""}},"playbook":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pbta/assets/icons/skills/light_02.webp","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hzrK1RFo81sGGJr3","name":"REJECTING INFLUENCE","permission":{"default":0,"PIYJckcNzA7ukurN":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When someone with Influence over you tells you who you are or how the world works, accept what they say or reject their influence.</p>\n<p>If you accept what they say, the GM adjusts your Labels accordingly; if you want to keep your Labels as they are, you must <strong>reject their Influence</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>REJECTING INFLUENCE</h2>\n<p>When you reject someone&rsquo;s Influence, roll.</p>\n<p>On a hit, you successfully hold to yourself and tune them out.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, choose two.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, choose one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>clear a condition or mark potential by immediately acting to prove them wrong</li>\n<li>shift one Label up and one Label down, your choice</li>\n<li>cancel their Influence and take +1 forward against them</li>\n</ul>\n<p>On a miss, their words hit you hard. Mark a condition, and the GM adjusts your Labels.</p>","requiresMove":"","moveType":"","moveGroup":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"key":"data.moveResults.failure.value","label":"Complications...","value":"<p>On a miss, their words hit you hard. Mark a condition, and the GM adjusts your Labels.</p>"},"partial":{"key":"data.moveResults.partial.value","label":"Partial success","value":"<p>On a hit, you successfully hold to yourself and tune them out.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, choose one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>clear a condition or mark potential by immediately acting to prove them wrong</li>\n<li>shift one Label up and one Label down, your choice</li>\n<li>cancel their Influence and take +1 forward against them</li>\n</ul>"},"success":{"key":"data.moveResults.success.value","label":"Success!","value":"<p>On a hit, you successfully hold to yourself and tune them out.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, choose two.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>clear a condition or mark potential by immediately acting to prove them wrong</li>\n<li>shift one Label up and one Label down, your choice</li>\n<li>cancel their Influence and take +1 forward against them</li>\n</ul>"}},"playbook":"","rollType":"prompt","rollMod":0},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pbta/assets/icons/skills/light_02.webp","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lBrUjR1A0t0GzWir","name":"Session Moves","permission":{"default":0,"PIYJckcNzA7ukurN":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>At the <strong>start of every session</strong>, the <strong>GM adds one Team to the pool</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At the <strong>end of every session, choose one:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Grow closer to the team. Explain who made you feel welcome; give Influence to that character and clear a condition or mark potential.</li>\n<li>Grow into your own image of yourself. Explain how you see yourself and why; shift one Label up and another down.</li>\n<li>Grow away from the team. Explain why you feel detached. Take Influence over you away from another character.</li>\n</ul>","requiresMove":"","moveType":"","moveGroup":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"key":"data.moveResults.failure.value","label":"Complications...","value":""},"partial":{"key":"data.moveResults.partial.value","label":"Partial success","value":""},"success":{"key":"data.moveResults.success.value","label":"Success!","value":""}},"playbook":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/sundries/books/book-embossed-steel-brown.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"SPENDING TEAM SELFISHLY","permission":{"default":0,"PIYJckcNzA7ukurN":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>SPENDING TEAM SELFISHLY</p>\n<p>When you act selfishly, say how your actions ignore or insult your teammates, remove one Team from the pool, and <strong>shift one Label up and one Label down</strong>, your choice.</p>\n<p>You can use this option after rolling to alter the Label you&rsquo;re rolling with.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Because you can act selfishly after you roll, this can boost a miss up to a hit, or a partial hit up to a full hit, by changing the Label you rolled with. All you have to do is spend the Team from the pool and describe your character doing something that ignores or insults your teammates.</p>\n<p>Generally, your teammates can determine whether they feel ignored or insulted by the selfish action, but the GM can push on it if it seems appropriate.</p>\n<p>Acting selfishly may save you when you can&rsquo;t be helped by anybody else, but it has a cost you can&rsquo;t avoid.</p>","requiresMove":"","moveType":"","moveGroup":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"key":"data.moveResults.failure.value","label":"Complications...","value":""},"partial":{"key":"data.moveResults.partial.value","label":"Partial success","value":""},"success":{"key":"data.moveResults.success.value","label":"Success!","value":""}},"playbook":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pbta/assets/icons/skills/violet_03.webp","effects":[],"_id":"rn9iciTwMa040zN1"}
{"name":"USING TEAM","permission":{"default":0,"PIYJckcNzA7ukurN":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<h1>USING TEAM</h1>\n<p>Anyone on the team can spend a Team out of the pool to give a teammate +1 on a move, after the roll. To do this, the spender has to be able to actually help&mdash;if you&rsquo;re in a completely different place from your teammate, then you can&rsquo;t spend Team to help, unless it makes sense in the fiction (a telepathic connection, maybe).</p>\n<p>Multiple teammates can spend Team from the pool to help on the same roll&mdash;even low rolls can be turned into hits when the whole group pitches in and there&rsquo;s enough Team in the pool.</p>\n<p>But each teammate can only spend one Team out of the pool for any single roll, and they still have to be able to actually help in the fiction.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>NPCs who are part of the team, whether temporarily or permanently, can also help. Players can spend Team from the pool on behalf of those NPCs. The players still have to spend one Team per NPC who helps, and the NPCs still have to be fictionally capable of helping. If the GM thinks the NPC wouldn&rsquo;t help, then they won&rsquo;t.</p>","requiresMove":"","moveType":"","moveGroup":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"key":"data.moveResults.failure.value","label":"Complications...","value":""},"partial":{"key":"data.moveResults.partial.value","label":"Partial success","value":""},"success":{"key":"data.moveResults.success.value","label":"Success!","value":""}},"playbook":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pbta/assets/icons/skills/violet_03.webp","effects":[],"_id":"y4vna72eWlTavfxq"}
